    <item>
      <title>At your funeral</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/repost/at-your-funeral/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 13 May 2025 18:55:43 +0200</pubDate>
      <author>mail@juju.casa (Julian Darío Gutierrez)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/repost/at-your-funeral/</guid>
      <description>Original post available here At your funeral, friends and family will argue over who gets your belongings.
People will talk about the food and the venue.
Your life will be summarized in 2-3 paragraphs.
Conversations will shift from your life to their lives.
Your friends will drive away thinking about what’s next on their to-do list.
Some people won&amp;rsquo;t be able to make it because &amp;ldquo;something came up.&amp;quot;
And most of the people you know today won’t even be there.</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://localhost:1313/repost/at-your-funeral/featured-funeral.jpg" />
    </item>
    
